<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> off one’s head • off one’s mind</xh5><p> <i>off one’s head</i>—(coll.) crazy or behaving as if mad <i>(also: out of one’s head):</i> He must be <u>off his head</u> to go jogging in this weather.</p><p> <div class="note">Note</div> The expression does not correlate in meaning with the phrase <b>off the top of one’s head</b>—<i>(coll.)</i> without proper consideration; in an impromptu manner: He was impetuous and inclined to think <u>off the top of his head</u> at times.</p><p> <i>off one’s mind—</i>1. said of smth. no longer causing worry or anxiety: And he had felt so happy.... His confession to June was <u>off his mind.</u> 2. <i>= off one’s head:</i> Politics is dirty. If so, one must be <u>off his mind</u> to enter politics.</p> </entry>
